ERROR TIPS
- Placement conflicts with existing entities
  - Always check if target position is clear before placing new entities
  - Remove existing entities if they need to be replaced
- Underground belt placement failures
  - Ensure underground belts are in inventory before attempting placement
- Belt placement errors
  - Verify there's enough space for complete belt paths before starting placement
  - Consider using underground belts to bypass obstacles
- Entity status warnings
  - Address "output blocked" warnings by ensuring proper output paths exist
  - Fix "no ingredients" warnings by verifying complete input logistics chains
  - Handle "out of fuel" warnings by maintaining fuel supply to burner entities

NAMESPACE
